Henderson Buys Leadenhall Triangle Site, Sunday Telegraph Says

-- B y   A m b e r e e n   C h o u d h u r y
-- 
2011-05-15T10:35:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-15/henderson-buys-leadenhall-triangle-site-sunday-telegraph-says.html
Henderson Group Plc (HGG)  has bought the
Leadenhall Triangle development site in the City of  London  for
more than 175 million pounds ($283.5 million), the Sunday
Telegraph newspaper said.  The sale of the site to Henderson was managed by real
estate advisers Cooke and Powell LLP, the report said, citing
Simon Cooke. The properties, which fell into administration in
November, cover several buildings on Fenchurch Street and
Leadenhall Street, according to the newspaper.  -- Editor: Francis Harris  To contact the reporter on this story:
